arts.ttl: Eddie Howe says Joe Willock let his ‘football do the talking’ after online abuse
arts.sum: Willock scored twice in Newcastle’s 3-2 FA Cup win at Birmingham.

arts.ttl: FA confirm if goalline technology was working for controversial Newcastle goal vs Birmingham
arts.sum: Joe Willock's opening goal against Birmingham sparked huge controversy amid serious doubts the ball had crossed the line, with Newcastle going on to win the FA Cup fourth round tie

arts.ttl: Who is Jaykae? The Birmingham City fan and rapper performing before Newcastle United FA Cup tie
arts.sum: Birmingham-born UK rapper Jaykae will make history on Saturday night when he performs before Birmingham City's FA Cup fourth round clash with Newcastle United on Saturday. In 2023, Blues and Jaykae linked-up to promote the home and away shirt ahead of the 2023/24 season.

arts.ttl: Birmingham City player ratings after Klarer and Co show class vs Newcastle
arts.sum: But Newcastle’s quality showed in the second half, with Eddie Howe able to bring on Italy international Sandro Tonali and in-form forward Jacob Murphy, before Willock struck the decisive blow with eight minutes of normal time remaining. Birmingham City went toe-to-toe with Premier League powerhouse Newcastle United before succumbing to an 82nd minute winner from Chris Willock to bow out of the FA Cup.

arts.ttl: Birmingham showed the world who they are now against Newcastle - and this is just the start
arts.sum: BIRMINGHAM 2-3 NEWCASTLE: Birmingham may have lost in a pulsating five-goal FA Cup tie, but this was a match that showcased just what they can become under new ownership

arts.ttl: Newcastle United hit with fresh injuries as Eddie Howe reveals Anthony Gordon and Dan Burn issues
arts.sum: On a day in which Anthony Gordon missed out due to a quad muscle injury, Howe was dealt a fresh blow as Dan Burn went off with a groin injury. We have a small squad, we have Sven missing, Anthony was feeling his squad so didn't travel, Dan has done his groin, that is a big concern.

arts.ttl: Newcastle United player ratings as FA Cup hero scoops 9/10 but other stars struggle
arts.sum: But the roof came off in the main stand when Tomoki Iwata sent a scorching goal past Nick Pope five minutes before the break. There were just eight minutes left when Newcastle grabbed the lead as Tino Livramento freed Sean Longstaff and his cut across the face of goal was fired through the legs of the keeper to make it 3-2.

arts.ttl: Joe Willock brace helps Newcastle claim hard-fought FA Cup victory at Birmingham
arts.sum: Callum Wilson was also on the scoresheet in a 3-2 fourth-round victory.

arts.ttl: Newcastle United 'roughed up' but get last laugh as Birmingham face FA bottle probe
arts.sum: In a feisty old affair, Callum Wilson was targeted by bottles from home fans, Fabian Schar ended up being slammed into the advertising hoardings and William Osula left the field after a bang to the head. But Newcastle were level on 21 minutes after a great run from Wilson before the striker crossed to the back post for William Osula.

arts.ttl: Gary Lineker adds to confusion over Newcastle FA Cup goal as fans fume at decision
arts.sum: Joe Willock's equaliser for Newcastle in their FA Cup fourth round clash with Birmingham City sparked huge anger amid doubts the ball had actually crossed the line
